       up too high yet.

09:49.920 --> 09:52.080
Don't get your hopes
       up too high yet.
Pay attention here, class.

09:52.080 --> 09:55.680
This is the "there are lots
of variables, no guarantees"
   part.

09:55.680 --> 09:59.120
What Dr Turner is saying
is that in-vitro fertilisation

09:59.120 --> 10:00.720
is in the experimental stage.

10:00.720 --> 10:03.440
Dr Chandler,
I have done this procedure.

10:03.440 --> 10:07.440
I think I can speak for myself.

10:13.720 --> 10:15.880
Are you OK?

10:15.880 --> 10:17.880
Weightlessness.

10:17.880 --> 10:20.040
Zero G.

10:20.040 --> 10:22.920
A misnomer technically,
where even in outer space

10:22.920 --> 10:25.040
a hint of gravity tugs at you.

10:25.040 --> 10:28.440
Houston control had to
   coax me back to the shuttle

10:28.440 --> 10:29.800
during my last spacewalk.

10:29.800 --> 10:33.760
It seems I was having too much
fun at the taxpayers' expense.

10:33.760 --> 10:37.760
When I left Orbiter to repair
the satellite, I stepped into

10:38.720 --> 10:40.040
a different world.

10:40.040 --> 10:43.560
The Earth below me, the stars.

10:43.560 --> 10:47.560
Outside the scope of human concerns.

10:49.840 --> 10:53.840
No longer just an earthling,
but a tiny planet.

10:59.360 --> 11:03.360
I look forward to my scheduled
walk during the mission next month.

11:05.560 --> 11:08.720
I'm sorry, we'd better
cut it right here.

11:08.720 --> 11:10.480
I spoke longer than I intended,

11:10.480 --> 11:14.480
and my wife and I have
  to return to Houston tonight.

11:14.960 --> 11:17.760
I'm proud to serve America
on the frontier of space.

11:17.760 --> 11:21.720
Thank you very much.

11:21.720 --> 11:25.720
     Let's meet an astronaut.

11:36.240 --> 11:40.240
Chuck!

11:42.240 --> 11:43.880
I'm a doctor.
What happened?

11:43.880 --> 11:47.880
I can't move my legs.

12:04.360 --> 12:06.640
OK, pupils equal and reactive.

12:06.640 --> 12:08.280
I want a full blood work up. &gt;

12:08.280 --> 12:10.200
X-ray of both
                  motor extremities.

12:10.200 --> 12:12.920
When did you first notice
the weakness in your legs?

12:12.920 --> 12:14.560
          A few days ago.

12:14.560 --> 12:17.760
There was a tingling sensation,
and everything felt heavy.

12:17.760 --> 12:20.120
I figured I was tired.
But it kept getting worse.

12:20.120 --> 12:21.680
Have you been ill recently?

12:21.680 --> 12:24.120
He had a cold a few weeks ago.
A bad one.

12:24.120 --> 12:25.800
       Everybody has colds.

12:25.800 --> 12:27.440
I've passed every
physical since

12:27.440 --> 12:30.000
I got out of the Academy,
without a hitch.

12:30.000 --> 12:31.120
          What is wrong?

12:31.120 --> 12:33.400
We'll know more after the tests.

12:33.400 --> 12:35.400
OK, what I want you to do now

12:35.400 --> 12:37.560
is squeeze my fingers
      as hard as you can.

12:37.560 --> 12:39.440
OK.

12:39.440 --> 12:42.560
Upper extremities, A-OK.

12:42.560 --> 12:46.560
Now try and lift your legs.

12:50.400 --> 12:53.080
OK, I want to do an LP.
Send the blood for a chem panel

12:53.080 --> 12:55.840
and viral titres.
Also have a respiratory therapist

12:55.840 --> 12:57.520
come down to measure capacity.

12:57.520 --> 12:58.720
Was it a stroke?

12:58.720 --> 13:01.080
A full stroke usually affects
  one side of the body.

13:01.080 --> 13:03.640
We're going to admit you,
    Colonel.

13:03.640 --> 13:05.560
I'll put in a menu request.

13:05.560 --> 13:09.480
Brian.
Do you want me to call NASA?

13:09.480 --> 13:11.600
    No! You know how they are.

13:11.600 --> 13:14.680
They'll ground you for a hangnail.

13:14.680 --> 13:15.960
       So it'll get better?

13:15.960 --> 13:17.840
There's no reason
       to believe it won't.

13:17.840 --> 13:21.840
You see.
Nothing to worry about.

13:25.040 --> 13:29.040
Elliott won't come out.
You talk to him.

13:29.200 --> 13:32.160
Hey!
We're talking heatstroke, pal.

13:32.160 --> 13:33.840
        You're vasodilated.

13:33.840 --> 13:37.840
Raise your core temperature high
enough to squash your brains.

13:38.840 --> 13:42.840
             Come on.

13:45.880 --> 13:48.320
I feel great.

13:48.320 --> 13:50.160
                           All right!

13:50.160 --> 13:53.760
You know, I never would have been
able to stick to this programme

13:53.760 --> 13:55.360
if it wasn't for you guys.

13:55.360 --> 13:57.720
We appreciate a challenge.

13:57.720 --> 14:00.040
So I get see Marcy again.

14:00.040 --> 14:02.080
Haven't seen her
for one whole month.

14:02.080 --> 14:03.800
        What kind of diet was she on?

14:03.800 --> 14:06.040
High protein.

14:06.040 --> 14:07.280
You know,

14:07.280 --> 14:11.280
my high school gym class voted
me most likely to blot out the sun.

14:12.360 --> 14:14.680
But this time,

14:14.680 --> 14:18.680
I really tried,
  I mean I really had willpower!

14:19.400 --> 14:20.560
                 The moment of truth.

14:20.560 --> 14:24.560
Oh, boy.

14:30.240 --> 14:33.040
Well?

