I've just received a report from
 the Residency Review Committee.

15:27.440 --> 15:29.200
They are hysterical because

15:29.200 --> 15:32.160
of the decline in elective surgeries
in both your departments.

15:32.160 --> 15:34.160
Electives are down.

15:34.160 --> 15:36.520
Everyone in plastics
sees plenty of action.

15:36.520 --> 15:39.560
This month, three
microsurgeries for limb reattachment.

15:39.560 --> 15:41.560
&lt; Which is why
the committee is up in arms.

15:41.560 --> 15:44.760
The residents aren't getting
   a full range of experience

15:44.760 --> 15:46.240
in cosmetic procedures.

15:46.240 --> 15:49.240
What about Andrea Fordham?
Probably the most extensive

15:49.240 --> 15:51.800
reconstruction work ever done
to a patient.

15:51.800 --> 15:54.080
Yesterday's news, Bob.

15:54.080 --> 15:57.160
I mean, let's face it,
this is a training hospital.

15:57.160 --> 16:00.720
If the residents aren't handling
a volume of the basics, they are not

16:00.720 --> 16:03.840
